text:
For Gawr Gura, the Ocean Star
In a blue corner of the virtual world, a sweet and vibrant voice was born. Small in size, but immense in brilliance. Gawr Gura wasn't just a VTuber, she was a shelter on difficult days, an unexpected smile in the midst of the storm. With every drawn-out "ah", every silly laugh, every moment of silence and affection, she built a home in millions of hearts. Today, the low tide takes with it the silhouette of a legend. And even knowing that every journey has its end... it still hurts. It hurts because loving hurts. But loving is also knowing how to let go with gratitude. She's leaving on May 1st, but she's not leaving us. Because those who touch souls never disappear. She's just swimming in other seas, until the day when maybe we'll find her again, with a different name, but the same sparkle in her eyes. Thank you, Gura. For the affection, the laughter, the sincere love that you didn't even know you gave. You were, and are, our little shark forever.ðŸ’™ðŸ’™ðŸ’™ðŸ’™ðŸ¦ˆ
